<body>
<h1>Express Authorization Example - Login</h1>

<p>
  This express website serves as an example of the "express-authorization" module.
  "express-authorization" is an express/connect middleware module for enforcing an
  Apache Shiro inspired authorization system.
</p>

<p>
  The <a href="asset">/assert</a> page is only available to users that have the "noun:verb" permission.
  "express-authorization" is used to enforce this rule.  Follow the links below to
  control your authentication state and attempt to visit the <a href="asset">/assert</a> page.
</p>

<form method="POST" action="/login">
  <div>
    <label>Username</label>
    <input name="username" value=""/>
  </div>
  <div>
    <label>Password</label>
    <input name="password" type="password"/>
  </div>
  <input type="submit" value="Login" />
</form>

</body>
</html>
